      "module_path": "ref_verify::scope_resolver",
      "docs": "Failure modes of RefVerifyScopeResolver::resolve after IN-01 artifact-existence-based refactor. InvalidLayerId variant removed (was only needed for TypeDesign { layer } context which is deleted by IN-02). Io covers genuine filesystem I/O errors when inspecting artifact paths (e.g. permission denied) and the fail-closed case where catalogues exist but spec.json is absent (IN-06, SoT Chain integrity violation). Consistent absence — spec.json absent (Chain1 zero pairs) or all catalogues absent (Chain2 zero pairs) — is NOT an error and does NOT return Err; those are zero-pair skip paths resolved without error. PartialCatalogues covers partial catalogue sets where some but not all layer catalogues exist (IN-05). Note: present-but-unparseable artifacts (IN-07) are NOT detected by the resolver — the resolver performs existence checks only; parse failures are detected downstream by pair_source/codec and surface as RefVerifyError::VerifierPort.",
