      "module_path": "ref_verify::scope_resolver",
      "docs": "Infrastructure adapter that resolves RefVerifyScope purely from artifact existence on disk (IN-01 / D1). After this track: resolve() takes only track_id and derives scope by checking whether spec.json and TDDD catalogue files exist; the context param is removed. resolve() performs existence checks only — it does NOT read or parse artifact contents. spec.json absent → Chain1 zero pairs (Phase 0 pass-through); all catalogues absent → Chain2 zero pairs; both present → All; partial catalogues → fail (IN-05); catalogue present + spec absent → fail (IN-06). Parse failures (IN-07) are NOT detected here; they are detected downstream by pair_source/codec as RefVerifyError::VerifierPort.",
